title: Residents escape burning home in Transcona - Winnipeg Free Press
text:
One firefighter suffered a minor wrist injury in a fire that broke out in one of the suites of a two-storey house at 415 Day St., in Transcona just after 6 a.m. today.
The fire started in the basement and spread to the kitchen of one of the suites, fire officials said this morning; three residents of that suite were already safely outside when firefighters arrived.
The cause of the fire is still under investigation.
